    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="292"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Rodriguez</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 26th ultimo, in which, after setting forth some secondary
                    points left in doubt by the arbitration of the boundary question between
                    Nicaragua and Costa Rica, you announce that under the provisions of a treaty
                    concluded recently between the two Governments the President of the United <pb
                        facs="0468" n="374" xml:id="pg_374"/> States is to be requested to appoint
                    an engineer to act as arbitrator in their settlement.</p>
                <p>The President will have much pleasure in acting upon the joint request of
                    Nicaragua and Costa Rica when made.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
